    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice half your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and set aside for garnish</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining green chilli[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> roughly, including the stems</p><p>Pick your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped chilli[es] </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with your<strong> ground cumin</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>mango chutney</strong> and the<strong> </strong>juice of half your <strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>mint leaves</strong>, <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>Hariyali-style marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, roughly chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and shred it roughly</p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped tomato[es]</strong> and <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> in a large bowl and set aside for serving \u2013 this is your <strong>salad</strong></p><p>In a separate bowl, combine the juice of the<strong> remaining lemon</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>zingy</strong> <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into strips</p><p>Season the <strong>chopped fish</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> seasoned fish </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> Hariyali-style marinade</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>marinated</strong> <strong>fish</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> marinated</strong> <strong>fish </strong>to the pan (along with any remaining hariyali marinade from the bowl!) and cook for 8-9 min or until cooked through, turning once halfway \u2013 this is your <strong>Hariyali-style fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/hariyali-style-cod-with-cauliflower-rice-and-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Hariyali-style fish </strong>with any <strong>cooked Hariyali-style marinade </strong>from the pan over the <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chilli rounds</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and drizzle the salad with the <strong>zingy lemon dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
